prediction.overall_explanation: Within this contract’s actual on-chain behavior, there are no concrete, exploitable security vulnerabilities that lead to fund loss, unauthorized access, or a meaningful DoS. The code makes no external calls, performs no ERC20 transfers, and does not custody or move assets; deposit/withdraw only update internal accounting variables (totalSupply, balanceOf, investedBalance). As a result, typical exploit classes (reentrancy, approval hijacking, token theft) are not practically actionable against this code as written.
